aix1AdminGbufXoffThreshold.name: aix1AdminGbufXoffThreshold
aix1AdminGbufXoffThreshold.description: The configured XOFF global flow control threshold. If zero and if aix1AdminGbufRecovThreshold is zero, the global flow control mechanism is disabled.

aix1AdminGbufRecovThreshold.name: aix1AdminGbufRecovThreshold
aix1AdminGbufRecovThreshold.description: The configured recovery global flow control threshold. If zero and if aix1AdminGbufXoffThreshold is zero, the global flow control mechanism is disabled.

aix1AdminRollover.name: aix1AdminRollover
aix1AdminRollover.description: This object has been depricated and remains in the MIB for backward compatibility.

aix1Bx25AdminCallDown.name: aix1Bx25AdminCallDown
aix1Bx25AdminCallDown.description: If set to off(2), an active BX.25 link will stay up after all calls are disconnected. If set to on(1), an active BX.25 link will drop and go into DMLOCK (see aix1Bx25AdminDMlock below) when all the link's backplane connections are terminated. This object is meaningful only when aix1ApplOperLinkMode is set to passive(2) on a given packet layer entity.

aix1Bx25AdminDMlock.name: aix1Bx25AdminDMlock
aix1Bx25AdminDMlock.description: The number of seconds to wait after a BX.25 passive link has gone inactive before allowing an outgoing call to attempt to bring up the link. Any outgoing call attempts will be rejected until the DMLOCK timer expires and the passive link returns to the standby mode. This object is meaningful only when aix1ApplOperLinkMode is set to passive(2) on a given packet layer entity.

aix1Bx25AdminLinkUp.name: aix1Bx25AdminLinkUp
aix1Bx25AdminLinkUp.description: The number of seconds to wait for a passive link to become active. This object is meaningful only when aix1ApplOperLinkMode is set to passive(2) on a given packet layer entity.

aix1StatErrX25InData.name: aix1StatErrX25InData
aix1StatErrX25InData.description: Number of data bytes from X.25 which were lost due to buffer failures.

aix1StatErrX25OutData.name: aix1StatErrX25OutData
aix1StatErrX25OutData.description: Number of data bytes from the FIFO which were discarded due to buffer failures.

aix1StatErrX25OutPkt.name: aix1StatErrX25OutPkt
aix1StatErrX25OutPkt.description: Number of messages from X.25 to GCOM which were lost due to some kind of resource failure in the GCOM library.

aix1StatErrX25OutChoked.name: aix1StatErrX25OutChoked
aix1StatErrX25OutChoked.description: Number of times a port has received a flow control stop message from GCOM(or perhaps from X.25), and thus entered the Choked state. This may not be indicative of a serious problem, but may also mean that data has been lost.

aix1StatErrPlogCount.name: aix1StatErrPlogCount
aix1StatErrPlogCount.description: Number of times an internal error routine has been called due to unexpected packets received from GCOM ( or X.25).

aix1StatErrGfctlXoffs.name: aix1StatErrGfctlXoffs
aix1StatErrGfctlXoffs.description: Number of times the global flow control mechanism attempted to back pressure data flow from the backplane.

aix1StatErrGfctlDiscards.name: aix1StatErrGfctlDiscards
aix1StatErrGfctlDiscards.description: Number of times the global flow control mechanism has detected a buffer level so low that it discarded data received from the backplane.

aix1StatErrUwteBadTrans.name: aix1StatErrUwteBadTrans
aix1StatErrUwteBadTrans.description: Number of unified window transactions with bad transaction codes received from CLC or a remote SLC. If this counter is non-zero, it indicated the presence of incompatible versions of firmware on the SLC and CLC, or a bug in either the SLC or CLC firmware.

aix1StatErrUwteBadFlds.name: aix1StatErrUwteBadFlds
aix1StatErrUwteBadFlds.description: Number of invalid fields received in unified window transactions. If this counter is non-zero, it indicates the presence of incompatible versions or a bug in either the SLC or CLC firmware.

aix1StatErrUwteMissingFlds.name: aix1StatErrUwteMissingFlds
aix1StatErrUwteMissingFlds.description: Number of required fields absent from received unified window transactions. If this counter is non-zero, it indicates the presence of incompatible versions or a bug in either the SLC or CLC firmware.

aix1StatErrLogOutLost.name: aix1StatErrLogOutLost
aix1StatErrLogOutLost.description: Number of outbound log messages discarded to avoid flooding the log. This arises because the SLC is attempting to generate log messages too frequently on a particular TDS or globally. When this occurs, the SLC will discard the log message and increment the counter. This is not a serious error, and typically occurs during periods of intense, repetitive logging activity.

aix1StatErrVcMuxErrs.name: aix1StatErrVcMuxErrs
aix1StatErrVcMuxErrs.description: Number of serious multiplexing errors which have occurred. Such an error generally involves an impossible value in an internal header or receipt of a message on the wrong internal channel.

aix1StatErrEmptyPktsRcv.name: aix1StatErrEmptyPktsRcv
aix1StatErrEmptyPktsRcv.description: Number of empty data packets received from the network.

aix1StatInCharsPerSec80s.name: aix1StatInCharsPerSec80s
aix1StatInCharsPerSec80s.description: The average number of data characters (characters in the data field of X.25 data packets) received from the network per second over the last 80 seconds.

aix1StatOutCharsPerSec80s.name: aix1StatOutCharsPerSec80s
aix1StatOutCharsPerSec80s.description: The average number of data characters (characters in the data field of X.25 data packets) transmitted to the network per second over the last 80 seconds.

aix1ApplAdminTable.name: aix1ApplAdminTable
aix1ApplAdminTable.description: The table of administrative elements which apply to an individual X.25 link above the packet layer.

aix1ApplAdminEntry.name: aix1ApplAdminEntry
aix1ApplAdminEntry.description: The addressing information for one of this X.25 link's administrative objects.

aix1ApplAdminIndex.name: aix1ApplAdminIndex
aix1ApplAdminIndex.description: The ifIndex value of the packet layer entity associated with these application level objects.

aix1ApplAdminLinkStart.name: aix1ApplAdminLinkStart
aix1ApplAdminLinkStart.description: Start or stop a link that's enabled by the standard MIB link status objects. If the link is not enabled by the standard MIB objects, a write to this object will have no effect. Stopping a link by writing to this object does not free significant resources, it just stops activity on the link.

aix1ApplAdminLinkMode.name: aix1ApplAdminLinkMode
aix1ApplAdminLinkMode.description: Determines whether link behaves as a normal X.25 link or a BX.25-style passive link. This is the most recently configured value of this attribute, and may not yet have taken effect. The current operating value is available as aix1ApplOperLinkMode.

aix1ApplAdminResetErrs.name: aix1ApplAdminResetErrs
aix1ApplAdminResetErrs.description: Writing the value resetCounters(2) to this object resets the per-link level 1 error counters. No other writes are accepted. They are aix1PhysStatRxCRCErrors, aix1PhysStatRxAborts, aix1PhysStatRxOverruns, aix1PhysStatTxAborts, aix1PhysStatTxUnderruns.

aix1ApplAdminXONXOFFProto.name: aix1ApplAdminXONXOFFProto
aix1ApplAdminXONXOFFProto.description: Determines whether XON/XOFF protocol processing is in effect by default on all virtual circuits on the link.

aix1ApplAdminNMAProto.name: aix1ApplAdminNMAProto
aix1ApplAdminNMAProto.description: Determines whether NMA protocol processing is in effect by default on all virtual circuits on the link.

aix1ApplAdminOPSINEProto.name: aix1ApplAdminOPSINEProto
aix1ApplAdminOPSINEProto.description: Determines whether OPSINE protocol processing is in effect by default on all virtual circuits on the link.

aix1ApplAdminTL1Proto.name: aix1ApplAdminTL1Proto
aix1ApplAdminTL1Proto.description: Determines whether TL1 protocol processing is in effect by default on all virtual circuits on the link.

aix1ApplAdminLinkDescription.name: aix1ApplAdminLinkDescription
aix1ApplAdminLinkDescription.description: A descriptive string associated with this link. This provides a place for the agent to supply any descriptive information about the use or owner of the link. A zero length value indicates that the agent doesn't have any additional information.

aix1ApplAdminLinkConnectionMode.name: aix1ApplAdminLinkConnectionMode
aix1ApplAdminLinkConnectionMode.description: Connect or disconnect a link that's enabled by the standard MIB linmk status objects. If the link is not enabled by the standard MIB objects, a write to this object will have no effect. Disconnecting a link by writing to this object does not free any resources, it marks the link as not connected, so that the link will not cause a level 4 (LINKDOWN) alarm to be generated.

aix1ApplOperTable.name: aix1ApplOperTable
aix1ApplOperTable.description: The table of operational elements which apply to an individual X.25 link above the packet layer.

aix1ApplOperEntry.name: aix1ApplOperEntry
aix1ApplOperEntry.description: The addressing information for one of this X.25 link's operational objects.

aix1ApplOperIndex.name: aix1ApplOperIndex
aix1ApplOperIndex.description: The ifIndex value of the packet level associated with these application level objects.

aix1ApplOperLinkMode.name: aix1ApplOperLinkMode
aix1ApplOperLinkMode.description: Determines whether link behaves as a normal X.25 link or a BX.25-style passive link. This is the mandatory operating value of this attribute. The most recently configured value is available as aix1ApplAdminLinkMode.

aix1ApplOperXONXOFFProto.name: aix1ApplOperXONXOFFProto
aix1ApplOperXONXOFFProto.description: Determines whether XON/XOFF protocol processing is in effect by default on all virtual circuits on the link.

aix1ApplOperNMAProto.name: aix1ApplOperNMAProto
aix1ApplOperNMAProto.description: Determines whether NMA protocol processing is in effect by default on all virtual circuits on the link.

aix1ApplOperOPSINEProto.name: aix1ApplOperOPSINEProto
aix1ApplOperOPSINEProto.description: Determines whether OPSINE protocol processing is in effect by default on all virtual circuits on the link.

aix1ApplOperTL1Proto.name: aix1ApplOperTL1Proto
aix1ApplOperTL1Proto.description: Determines whether TL1 protocol processing is in effect by default on all virtual circuits on the link.

aix1ApplOperLinkDescription.name: aix1ApplOperLinkDescription
aix1ApplOperLinkDescription.description: A descriptive string associated with this link. This provides a place for the agent to supply any descriptive information about the use or owner of the link. A zero length value indicates that the agent doesn't have any additional information.

aix1ApplOperLinkConnectionMode.name: aix1ApplOperLinkConnectionMode
aix1ApplOperLinkConnectionMode.description: Determines whether the link is currently disconnected, connected or has been reconnected after it was disconnected.

aix1PktAdminTable.name: aix1PktAdminTable
aix1PktAdminTable.description: The table of administrative elements which apply to an individual X.25 link at the packet layer.

aix1PktAdminEntry.name: aix1PktAdminEntry
aix1PktAdminEntry.description: The addressing information for one of this X.25 link's packet layer administrative objects.

aix1PktAdminIndex.name: aix1PktAdminIndex
aix1PktAdminIndex.description: The ifIndex value of the packet layer entity associated with these objects.

aix1PktAdminConformanceMode.name: aix1PktAdminConformanceMode
aix1PktAdminConformanceMode.description: The configured conformance testing mode to which X.25's behavior will adhere. This value may not have taken effect. The value with which the SLC is currently operating is the value of aix1OperConformanceMode.

aix1PktAdminDBit.name: aix1PktAdminDBit
aix1PktAdminDBit.description: Determines whether the packet level will allow the D-bit in call setup packets.

aix1PktAdminQBitMBit.name: aix1PktAdminQBitMBit
aix1PktAdminQBitMBit.description: Determines whether the packet level will check for consistency in the use of Q and M bits, i. e. that the value of the Q-bit is the same in every packet of an M-bit sequence.

aix1PktAdminUseRejectPkts.name: aix1PktAdminUseRejectPkts
aix1PktAdminUseRejectPkts.description: Enables and disables the use of packet retransmission. If the packet level is acting as a DTE it will send a REJ packet in response to a data packet received out of sequence. If the packet level is acting as a DCE, it will accept a REJ packet and retransmit the requested data packet(s).

aix1PktAdminSendInitialRestart.name: aix1PktAdminSendInitialRestart
aix1PktAdminSendInitialRestart.description: Enables and disables sending of an initial restart request packet when the link comes up.

aix1PktAdminStdsBody.name: aix1PktAdminStdsBody
aix1PktAdminStdsBody.description: Selects between ISO and CCITT packet level specifications.

aix1PktAdminFacilChecking.name: aix1PktAdminFacilChecking
aix1PktAdminFacilChecking.description: Enables and disables packet level checking of the facilities field of call processing packets for validity.

aix1PktAdminUndefinedFacils.name: aix1PktAdminUndefinedFacils
aix1PktAdminUndefinedFacils.description: Enables and disables packet level allowing undefined facilities to appear in the facilities field of call processing packets.

aix1PktAdminDefMaxPktSize.name: aix1PktAdminDefMaxPktSize
aix1PktAdminDefMaxPktSize.description: The maximum packet size to use for all calls placed on this packet layer entity. If aix1PktAdminNegPktSize is set to negotiate(2), this will be the proposed value for calls placed on the packet level entitry.

aix1PktAdminDefWindowSize.name: aix1PktAdminDefWindowSize
aix1PktAdminDefWindowSize.description: The maximum packet level window size to use on this PLE. If aix1PktAdminNegWindowSize is set to negotiate(2), this will be the proposed value for calls placed on the packet layer entity.

aix1PktAdminNegMaxPktSize.name: aix1PktAdminNegMaxPktSize
aix1PktAdminNegMaxPktSize.description: Determines whether this PLE will originate calls which negotiate packet size.

aix1PktAdminNegWindowSize.name: aix1PktAdminNegWindowSize
aix1PktAdminNegWindowSize.description: Determines whether this PLE will originate calls which negotiate window size.

aix1PktAdminPacketizingTimer.name: aix1PktAdminPacketizingTimer
aix1PktAdminPacketizingTimer.description: The interval from the time of receipt of the first character from the TDM backplane to transmission of a block of characters to the X.25 protocol stack for transmission in a data packet to the network. In 100ths of a second. This value is not meaningful on backplane connections on which escape framing, TL1 packetizing, or programmable forwarding characters are active.

aix1PktAdminPVCOffset.name: aix1PktAdminPVCOffset
aix1PktAdminPVCOffset.description: Specifies an offset that gets added to the PVC logical channel range specified by x25AdmnMaxActiveCircuits and x25AdmnNumberPVCs from RFC 1382.

aix1PktAdminSVCOffset.name: aix1PktAdminSVCOffset
aix1PktAdminSVCOffset.description: Specifies an offset that gets added to the SVC logical channel range specified by x25AdmnMaxActiveCircuits and x25AdmnNumberPVCs from RFC 1382.

aix1PktOperTable.name: aix1PktOperTable
aix1PktOperTable.description: The table of operational elements which apply to an individual X.25 link at the packet layer.

aix1PktOperEntry.name: aix1PktOperEntry
aix1PktOperEntry.description: The addressing information for one of this X.25 link's packet layer operational objects.

aix1PktOperIndex.name: aix1PktOperIndex
aix1PktOperIndex.description: The ifIndex value of the packet level associated with these objects.

aix1PktOperConformanceMode.name: aix1PktOperConformanceMode
aix1PktOperConformanceMode.description: The conformance testing mode to which X.25's behavior will adhere. This is the currently operational value.

aix1PktOperDBit.name: aix1PktOperDBit
aix1PktOperDBit.description: Determines whether the packet level will allow the D-bit in call setup packets.

aix1PktOperQBitMBit.name: aix1PktOperQBitMBit
aix1PktOperQBitMBit.description: Determines whether the packet level will check for consistency in the use of Q and M bits, i. e. that the value of the Q-bit is the same in every packet of an M-bit sequence.

aix1PktOperUseRejectPkts.name: aix1PktOperUseRejectPkts
aix1PktOperUseRejectPkts.description: Enables and disables the use of packet retransmission. If the packet level is acting as a DTE it will send a REJ packet in response to a data packet received out of sequence. If the packet level is acting as a DCE, it will accept a REJ packet and retransmit the requested data packet(s).

aix1PktOperSendInitialRestart.name: aix1PktOperSendInitialRestart
aix1PktOperSendInitialRestart.description: Enables and disables sending of an initial restart request packet when the link comes up.

aix1PktOperStdsBody.name: aix1PktOperStdsBody
aix1PktOperStdsBody.description: Selects between ISO and CCITT packet level specifications.

aix1PktOperFacilChecking.name: aix1PktOperFacilChecking
aix1PktOperFacilChecking.description: Enables and disables packet level checking of the facilities field of call processing packets for validity.

aix1PktOperUndefinedFacils.name: aix1PktOperUndefinedFacils
aix1PktOperUndefinedFacils.description: Enables and disables packet level allowing undefined facilities to appear in the facilities field of call processing packets.

aix1PktOperDefMaxPktSize.name: aix1PktOperDefMaxPktSize
aix1PktOperDefMaxPktSize.description: The maximum packet size to use for all calls placed on this packet layer entity. If aix1PktOperNegPktSize is set to negotiate(2), this will be the proposed value for calls placed on the packett layer entity.

aix1PktOperDefWindowSize.name: aix1PktOperDefWindowSize
aix1PktOperDefWindowSize.description: The maximum packet level window size to use for all calls placed on this packet layer entity. If aix1PktOperNegWindowSize is set to negotiate(2), this will be the proposed value for calls placed on the packet layer entity.

aix1PktOperNegMaxPktSize.name: aix1PktOperNegMaxPktSize
aix1PktOperNegMaxPktSize.description: Determines whether this packet layer entity will originate calls which negotiate packet size.

aix1PktOperNegWindowSize.name: aix1PktOperNegWindowSize
aix1PktOperNegWindowSize.description: Determines whether this packet layer entity will originate calls which negotiate window size.

aix1PktOperPacketizingTimer.name: aix1PktOperPacketizingTimer
aix1PktOperPacketizingTimer.description: The interval from the time of receipt of the first character from the TDM backplane to transmission of a block of characters to the X.25 protocol stack for transmission in a data packet to the network. In 100ths of a second. This value is not meaningful on backplane connections on which escape framing, TL1 packetizing, or programmable forwarding characters are active.

aix1PktOperPVCOffset.name: aix1PktOperPVCOffset
aix1PktOperPVCOffset.description: Specifies an offset that gets added to the PVC logical channel range specified by x25AdmnMaxActiveCircuits and x25AdmnNumberPVCs from RFC 1382.

aix1PktOperSVCOffset.name: aix1PktOperSVCOffset
aix1PktOperSVCOffset.description: Specifies an offset that gets added to the SVC logical channel range specified by x25AdmnMaxActiveCircuits and x25AdmnNumberPVCs from RFC 1382.

aix1PktStatTable.name: aix1PktStatTable
aix1PktStatTable.description: The table of statistical elements which apply to an individual X.25 link at the packet layer.

aix1PktStatEntry.name: aix1PktStatEntry
aix1PktStatEntry.description: The addressing information for one of this X.25 link's packet layer statistical objects.

aix1PktStatIndex.name: aix1PktStatIndex
aix1PktStatIndex.description: The ifIndex value of the packet layer entity associated with these objects.

aix1PktStatInCharsPerSec80s.name: aix1PktStatInCharsPerSec80s
aix1PktStatInCharsPerSec80s.description: The average number of data characters (characters in the data field of X.25 data packets) received from the network per second over the last 80 seconds by this packet layer entity.

aix1PktStatOutCharsPerSec80s.name: aix1PktStatOutCharsPerSec80s
aix1PktStatOutCharsPerSec80s.description: The average number of data characters (characters in the data field of X.25 data packets) transmitted to the network per second over the last 80 seconds by this packet layer entity.

aix1FrmAdminTable.name: aix1FrmAdminTable
aix1FrmAdminTable.description: The table of administrative elements which apply to an individual X.25 link at the frame layer.

aix1FrmAdminEntry.name: aix1FrmAdminEntry
aix1FrmAdminEntry.description: The addressing information for one of this X.25 link's frame layer administrative objects.

aix1FrmAdminIndex.name: aix1FrmAdminIndex
aix1FrmAdminIndex.description: The ifIndex value of the frame layer entity associated with these objects.

aix1FrmAdminIdleRRs.name: aix1FrmAdminIdleRRs
aix1FrmAdminIdleRRs.description: Enables and disables transmission of idle Receive Ready frames by the frame layer.

aix1FrmAdminRandomizeT1.name: aix1FrmAdminRandomizeT1
aix1FrmAdminRandomizeT1.description: Enables and disables the introduction of random jitter into the frame layer's T1 timer to avoid T1 timer synchronization with the remote frame layer.

aix1FrmOperTable.name: aix1FrmOperTable
aix1FrmOperTable.description: The table of operational elements which apply to an individual X.25 link at the frame layer.

aix1FrmOperEntry.name: aix1FrmOperEntry
aix1FrmOperEntry.description: The addressing information for one of this X.25 link's frame layer operational objects.

aix1FrmOperIndex.name: aix1FrmOperIndex
aix1FrmOperIndex.description: The ifIndex value of the frame level associated with these objects.

aix1FrmOperIdleRRs.name: aix1FrmOperIdleRRs
aix1FrmOperIdleRRs.description: Enables and disables transmission of idle Receive Ready frames by the frame layer.

aix1FrmOperRandomizeT1.name: aix1FrmOperRandomizeT1
aix1FrmOperRandomizeT1.description: Enables and disables the introduction of random jitter into the frame layer's T1 timer to avoid T1 timer synchronization with the remote frame layer.

aix1PhysAdminTable.name: aix1PhysAdminTable
aix1PhysAdminTable.description: The table of administrative elements which apply to an individual X.25 link at the physical layer.

aix1PhysAdminEntry.name: aix1PhysAdminEntry
aix1PhysAdminEntry.description: The addressing information for one of this X.25 link's physical layer administrative objects.

aix1PhysAdminIndex.name: aix1PhysAdminIndex
aix1PhysAdminIndex.description: The ifIndex value of the physical port associated with these objects.

aix1PhysAdminInterFrameDelayStatus.name: aix1PhysAdminInterFrameDelayStatus
aix1PhysAdminInterFrameDelayStatus.description: Enables and disables a delay period between transmitted frames.

aix1PhysAdminInterFrameDelayInterval.name: aix1PhysAdminInterFrameDelayInterval
aix1PhysAdminInterFrameDelayInterval.description: Sets the interframe delay interval. This value is effective only if aix1PhysAdminInterFrameDelayStatus is set to ifdEnabled(2). This value is expressed in microseconds, with 100 microsecond granularity (it's truncated to the nearest 100 microseconds).

aix1PhysAdminT1LineBuildOut.name: aix1PhysAdminT1LineBuildOut
aix1PhysAdminT1LineBuildOut.description: The T1 line build out value. The specified syntax represents ranges of line length expressed in feet.

aix1PhysOperTable.name: aix1PhysOperTable
aix1PhysOperTable.description: The table of operational elements which apply to an individual X.25 link at the physical layer.

aix1PhysOperEntry.name: aix1PhysOperEntry
aix1PhysOperEntry.description: The addressing information for one of this X.25 link's physical layer operational objects.

aix1PhysOperIndex.name: aix1PhysOperIndex
aix1PhysOperIndex.description: The ifIndex value of the physical port associated with these objects.

aix1PhysOperInterFrameDelayStatus.name: aix1PhysOperInterFrameDelayStatus
aix1PhysOperInterFrameDelayStatus.description: Enables and disables a delay period between transmitted frames.

aix1PhysOperInterFrameDelayInterval.name: aix1PhysOperInterFrameDelayInterval
aix1PhysOperInterFrameDelayInterval.description: Sets the interframe delay interval. This value is effective only if aix1PhysAdminInterFrameDelayStatus is set to ifdEnabled(2). This value is expressed in microseconds, with 100 microsecond granularity (it's truncated to the nearest 100 microseconds).

aix1PhysOperT1LineBuildOut.name: aix1PhysOperT1LineBuildOut
aix1PhysOperT1LineBuildOut.description: The T1 line build out value. The specified syntax represents ranges of line length expressed in feet.

aix1PhysStatTable.name: aix1PhysStatTable
aix1PhysStatTable.description: The table of statistical elements which apply to an individual X.25 link at the physical layer.

aix1PhysStatEntry.name: aix1PhysStatEntry
aix1PhysStatEntry.description: The addressing information for one of this X.25 link's physical layer statistical objects.

aix1PhysStatIndex.name: aix1PhysStatIndex
aix1PhysStatIndex.description: The ifIndex value of the physical port associated with these objects.

aix1PhysStatTxAborts.name: aix1PhysStatTxAborts
aix1PhysStatTxAborts.description: The number of abort sequences transmitted on the serial interfaces. This is a proprietary object because the RS232-like MIB (RFC 1659) doesn't define a similar object! RFC 1659 defines a counter for receive aborts, but not transmit aborts.

aix1CircuitTable.name: aix1CircuitTable
aix1CircuitTable.description: The table of objects which maps logical channel number and packet level ifIndex number to Virtual Connection(VC) number.

aix1CircuitEntry.name: aix1CircuitEntry
aix1CircuitEntry.description: The addressing information for the VC Circuit table.

aix1CircuitLinkId.name: aix1CircuitLinkId
aix1CircuitLinkId.description: The ifindex value of the packet layer entity.

aix1CircuitState.name: aix1CircuitState
aix1CircuitState.description: The call processing state of the local Virtual Connection. This is not a standard packet level state. This is the call processing state of the AI version 7 system firmware that mediates between the X.25 protocol stack and AISwitch internal connection mechanisms.

aix1CircuitConType.name: aix1CircuitConType
aix1CircuitConType.description: The type of connection currently supported by the VC.

aix1CircuitBCNumber.name: aix1CircuitBCNumber
aix1CircuitBCNumber.description: The number of the Bus Connection with which this VC is associated.

aix1CircuitUserData.name: aix1CircuitUserData
aix1CircuitUserData.description: The user data that was sent or received in the call request.

aix1CircuitRemoteBasePort.name: aix1CircuitRemoteBasePort
aix1CircuitRemoteBasePort.description: The baseport of the card to which the SLC is connected across the backplane. This value is meaningful only when this VC is multiplexed to the other SLC. If not, the value returned is -1.

aix1CircuitRemoteVCNumber.name: aix1CircuitRemoteVCNumber
aix1CircuitRemoteVCNumber.description: The Virtual Connection number of the VC on the remote SLC to which this VC is connected. This value is meaningful only on multiplexed VCs.

aix1CircuitPktsSent.name: aix1CircuitPktsSent
aix1CircuitPktsSent.description: The number of packets sent to the packet level by the AI version 7 system software. This counts all kinds of packets, not just data packets.

aix1CircuitPktsRcvd.name: aix1CircuitPktsRcvd
aix1CircuitPktsRcvd.description: The number of packets received from the packet level by the AI version 7 system software. This counts all kinds of packets, not just data packets.

aix1CircuitOperPVCType.name: aix1CircuitOperPVCType
aix1CircuitOperPVCType.description: Defines the relationship between a PVC and the connection-oriented AISwitch TDM backplane. The three types represented are defined as follows: Active: initiates connections across the backplane at an interval defined by the timer. Passive: waits to respond to a connection attempt across the backplane. Uses timer to wait for reset confirm from network. Accepts backplane connection if it receives reset confirmation in time. Connect on Activity: initiates connection across backplane upon the receipt of data from the network. Forwards received data once connection is established. Disconnects backplane connection if a timer interval passes with no data activity in either direction. This object will return the value none(1) if the value of aix1CircuitConType for this VC is not pvc(11). This object reflects the current operational value of this parameter.
